[panting and grunting]

00:45.845 --> 00:47.221
[sobs]

00:55.221 --> 00:56.239
[breathing heavily]

01:14.239 --> 01:16.251
[whimpering softly]

01:59.251 --> 02:00.925
[gun clicking empty]

02:40.925 --> 02:42.400
[gun fires]

02:48.400 --> 02:50.240
[gun hammer cocks]

02:54.240 --> 02:56.008
[breathing heavily]

02:57.008 --> 02:59.510
Fuck you!

02:59.511 --> 03:01.713
[gunshot]

03:01.714 --> 03:04.458
["Your One and Only Love"
by Jackie Wilson plays]

03:12.458 --> 03:17.532
♪ Your one and only love ♪

03:20.532 --> 03:25.938
♪ That's all I want to be ♪

03:26.938 --> 03:31.544
♪ Your one and only love ♪

03:33.544 --> 03:37.785
♪ Through all eternity ♪

03:39.785 --> 03:44.557
♪ All that I'm dreaming of ♪

03:46.557 --> 03:51.798
♪ Is to be yours alone ♪

03:52.798 --> 03:57.571
♪ Your one and only love ♪

03:59.571 --> 04:04.315
♪ The one you call your own ♪

04:09.315 --> 04:11.016
♪ To love you always ♪

04:12.016 --> 04:15.485
♪ Always and always ♪

04:15.486 --> 04:20.558
♪ Gladly, I vow ♪

04:20.559 --> 04:21.958
[car door closes]

04:21.959 --> 04:25.395
♪ To love you madly ♪

04:25.396 --> 04:28.066
♪ To need you badly ♪

04:28.067 --> 04:32.639
♪ Just as I
need you now ♪

04:34.639 --> 04:39.913
♪ Your one and only love ♪

04:40.913 --> 04:45.920
♪ Someday someone will be ♪

04:47.920 --> 04:53.857
♪ So, darling
take my love ♪

04:53.858 --> 04:58.528
♪ And fall in love ♪

04:58.529 --> 05:02.700
♪ With ♪

05:02.701 --> 05:09.716
♪ Me ♪

05:17.716 --> 05:19.014
[blues music plays]

05:50.014 --> 05:51.651
Off-suit deuce, 7.

05:53.651 --> 05:55.919
That's an unlucky hand.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.533
Hell, it's the worst hand.

06:08.533 --> 06:10.605
If you want this shithole back,
it's yours.

06:13.605 --> 06:15.138
No, Roy.

06:15.139 --> 06:17.812
That's not why I'm here.

06:19.812 --> 06:22.649
Then what are you doing
in my house?

06:24.649 --> 06:27.518
I need your help.

06:27.519 --> 06:29.619
[lighter scratches]

06:29.620 --> 06:30.955
Didn't you get my postcard?

06:30.956 --> 06:32.523
Yeah.

06:32.524 --> 06:35.163
A year ago, reported you
fucking dead.

06:39.163 --> 06:40.163
[cards shuffling]

06:46.103 --> 06:48.104
[sighs]

06:48.105 --> 06:50.843
Open it.

06:51.843 --> 06:53.904
Go on, open it.

07:18.904 --> 07:20.705
Is this for real?

07:20.706 --> 07:21.843
You're holding it.

07:25.843 --> 07:27.985
Where'd you get this?

07:32.985 --> 07:34.654
Well...

07:35.654 --> 07:36.661
[lighter scratches]

07:43.661 --> 07:47.532
I just lost my last 100
on a 1-3 no limit.

07:47.533 --> 07:49.934
Made a stupid call.

07:49.935 --> 07:52.971
Left with 5 bucks
and a bad taste in my mouth.

07:53.971 --> 07:55.705
But...

07:55.706 --> 07:58.842
of course, I'm still
itching to play.

07:58.843 --> 08:01.081
Figured I might as well
finish off on penny slots.

08:04.081 --> 08:06.249
So a minute later
I'm back on the floor.

08:06.250 --> 08:08.753
It's about 2:00 a.m.
Place is thinning out.

08:08.754 --> 08:10.054
[coins clattering]

08:10.055 --> 08:12.123
Some dealers.

08:12.124 --> 08:14.325
Floor men.

08:14.326 --> 08:16.964
One cashier.

08:18.964 --> 08:22.970
And a handful of retirees
just burning up their pensions.

08:24.970 --> 08:26.571
And there I am.

08:26.572 --> 08:28.873
Looking for a spot.

08:28.874 --> 08:31.822
For a chance just to turn
my luck around.

08:44.822 --> 08:47.925
I find a machine, sit down.
Nothing fancy.

08:47.926 --> 08:50.127
No gimmick screen,
nothing like that.

08:50.128 --> 08:54.230
And as I sit down
I notice this...

08:54.231 --> 08:57.307
this strange cowboy guy.

09:03.307 --> 09:05.276
And I don't pay
too much attention,

09:05.277 --> 09:06.637
because I'm just there
to flip my 5

09:07.011 --> 09:09.948
and enjoy the ringing
of the bell as I keep winning.

09:10.948 --> 09:13.316
But it don't work out that way.

09:13.317 --> 09:16.787
I strike out faster
than a first-season rookie,

09:16.788 --> 09:20.226
before the waitress even has
a chance to make her first pass.

09:21.226 --> 09:23.226
♪ You know ♪

09:23.227 --> 09:27.364
♪ My new broom knows
how to please, baby ♪

09:27.365 --> 09:32.643
♪ And my old broom
knows how to squeeze ♪

09:37.643 --> 09:41.280
♪ My new love looks good ♪

09:43.280 --> 09:47.851
♪ And she knows
just how to please ♪

09:47.852 --> 09:49.720
♪ Lord have mercy ♪

09:49.721 --> 09:52.856
♪ I wonder, can I get
a witness tonight, children? ♪

09:52.857 --> 09:57.197
♪ I said, my new love
looks good, baby ♪

09:59.197 --> 10:03.735
♪ Lord, she knows
just how to please ♪

10:04.735 --> 10:08.239
[loud explosions and gunfire]

10:08.240 --> 10:11.274
[people screaming distantly]

10:11.275 --> 10:13.066
[alarm rings]

10:34.066 --> 10:36.267
[panting]

10:36.268 --> 10:37.468
[Bill]
All of a sudden,

10:37.469 --> 10:39.873
all I want to do is go home.

10:41.873 --> 10:43.715
[man]
Get out.

10:49.715 --> 10:51.485
Walk. Walk!

10:54.485 --> 10:56.495
Get on your knees.

11:03.495 --> 11:05.131
[gunshot]

11:07.131 --> 11:09.808
[both grunting]

11:17.808 --> 11:19.124
[indistinct grunt]

11:32.124 --> 11:34.505
[breathing heavily]

11:46.505 --> 11:48.428
[coughs]

12:10.428 --> 12:13.062
[starts engine]

12:13.063 --> 12:16.133
[Bill]
In the bag, 10,000 hard cash

12:16.134 --> 12:18.969
and almost 100,000 in chips.

12:18.970 --> 12:21.806
When I get home,
I'm fucking panicked.

12:21.807 --> 12:23.474
I'm thinking about
what I just did,

12:23.475 --> 12:26.042
thinking about this thing
that I now have.

12:26.043 --> 12:28.979
And what about the cops?

12:28.980 --> 12:30.848
I mean, if they come
looking for this,

12:30.849 --> 12:33.989
I'm going to get pegged
for something that I didn't do.

13:10.989 --> 13:13.066
[inhales and exhales deeply]

13:21.066 --> 13:23.504
I didn't want to involve you.

13:26.504 --> 13:29.643
And I really didn't want
to involve your sister.

13:31.643 --> 13:33.446
So...

13:34.446 --> 13:35.565
I ran.

13:53.565 --> 13:55.532
Does my sister know?

13:55.533 --> 13:58.437
No. Only you.

13:59.437 --> 14:01.171
Keep it that way.

14:01.172 --> 14:02.476
Why?

14:04.476 --> 14:06.609
Why? Because we thought
you were fucking dead,

14:06.610 --> 14:07.981
that's fucking why.

14:10.981 --> 14:12.682
Well, I wasn't.

14:12.683 --> 14:14.618
Yeah...

14:14.619 --> 14:16.158
you were.

14:21.158 --> 14:23.029
If that's the way
you feel about it...

14:25.029 --> 14:27.067
I'm really sorry I wasted
your fucking time.

14:30.067 --> 14:31.708
How many zeros is that?

14:37.708 --> 14:39.249
It's five zeros.

14:44.249 --> 14:46.332
[country music plays]

15:01.332 --> 15:05.034
♪ You dropped me off ♪

15:05.035 --> 15:09.406
♪ In Lonesomeville ♪

15:09.407 --> 15:15.149
♪ A place where only
lonely people live ♪

15:18.149 --> 15:22.186
♪ The many hearts
you've broken ♪

15:22.187 --> 15:26.123
♪ Live here in Lonesomeville ♪

15:26.124 --> 15:28.624
♪ And the only thing
that's left... ♪

15:28.625 --> 15:31.128
[Roy]
So, what's the plan?

15:31.129 --> 15:33.430
- Yo.
- [knocks]

15:33.431 --> 15:35.499
Man, you hear me?

15:35.500 --> 15:38.502
I think we should
avoid the casinos.

15:38.503 --> 15:41.205
I don't even know
if the chips are marked.

15:41.206 --> 15:43.172
You don't even want to try?

15:43.173 --> 15:45.341
You waited this long,
you might as well try.

15:45.342 --> 15:46.744
Well...

15:46.745 --> 15:48.579
if I do this,

15:48.580 --> 15:51.114
I go all the way.

15:51.115 --> 15:52.782
Well, then we get someone
to buy the lot.

15:52.783 --> 15:54.551
- Discount special.
- I thought of that.

15:54.552 --> 15:55.712
- And?
- I don't know anybody.

15:56.020 --> 15:57.488
- Man, I got people?
- What people?

15:57.489 --> 15:59.322
Zack down at the gas station?

15:59.323 --> 16:01.258
That fucking burnout.
Is that who you know?

16:01.259 --> 16:02.725
Christ, Roy,
I didn't want to have you

16:02.726 --> 16:04.327
involved in this
in the first place,

16:04.328 --> 16:07.630
but you're the only fucking
person I can trust.

16:07.631 --> 16:10.437
And that's saying a lot.

16:12.437 --> 16:14.303
Yeah.

16:14.304 --> 16:16.373
Well...

16:16.374 --> 16:18.075
I'm already involved.

16:18.076 --> 16:20.444
Now, I know you're lying
to me, bitch.

16:20.445 --> 16:22.317
Now give me the fucking money.

16:26.317 --> 16:28.118
I'm just fucking with you.

16:28.119 --> 16:29.552
[laughs]

16:29.553 --> 16:30.754
So, what do you think?

16:30.755 --> 16:32.189
Pretty nice, huh?

16:32.190 --> 16:34.090
Shit, man, relax.

16:34.091 --> 16:36.197
Fucking idiot.

16:40.197 --> 16:41.598
It's loaded.

16:41.599 --> 16:43.533
No shit.
It's our insurance policy.

16:43.534 --> 16:47.370
This is the difference between
five years to life in prison.

16:47.371 --> 16:49.306
Why are you fucking around?

16:49.307 --> 16:51.374
This shit is like moving
a dead body,

16:51.375 --> 16:53.343
and I do not need you
carrying that weight around

16:53.344 --> 16:55.144
the rest of your goddamned life,
do you hear me?

16:55.145 --> 16:56.446
- Dead body?
- Yeah.

16:56.447 --> 16:58.481
Dead bodies ain't got
no big-ass payoffs,

16:58.482 --> 17:01.085
-so let me worry
about my own shit.
-Shut the fuck up.

17:01.086 --> 17:03.153
Shut up.

17:03.154 --> 17:05.556
It was stupid, Roy.

17:05.557 --> 17:07.259
Fuck!

17:08.259 --> 17:10.259
[sighs]

17:10.260 --> 17:11.498
Here.

17:13.498 --> 17:15.468
Yo, keep it.

17:16.468 --> 17:18.335
I was just playing.

17:18.336 --> 17:20.679
Relax.

17:27.679 --> 17:31.852
♪ There's no one here
but us children ♪

17:33.852 --> 17:35.818
[Bill]
There's 100 large.

17:35.819 --> 17:38.521
We want 50. That's a fair trade.
That's our offer.

17:38.522 --> 17:40.556
[Dick]
100's a long raw potato.

17:40.557 --> 17:42.625
It ain't gonna be easy.

17:42.626 --> 17:44.894
Where'd you get the chips from?

17:44.895 --> 17:46.596
[Bill]
It doesn't matter right now.

17:46.597 --> 17:48.265
Money's money.

17:48.266 --> 17:50.233
[Dick]
What's your fucking point, son?

17:50.234 --> 17:51.835
[Bill]
My point is,

17:51.836 --> 17:54.805
if you can't help
then we'll go to someone else.

17:54.806 --> 17:56.405
[laughs]

17:56.406 --> 17:59.778
[grunting on cartoon]

18:00.778 --> 18:02.613
My point is...

18:02.614 --> 18:04.413
fuck stain...

18:04.414 --> 18:06.549
just because it looks good,

18:06.550 --> 18:09.353
that don't make it good.

18:09.354 --> 18:11.755
[Bill]
Well, that's the deal.

18:11.756 --> 18:14.191
You buy the chips,
you take the risk.

18:14.192 --> 18:16.692
[Dick]
You ain't the gambling type,
are you?

18:16.693 --> 18:20.203
You see, I'm an Omaha man
myself.

18:26.203 --> 18:28.838
All right.

18:28.839 --> 18:32.543
But understand this, all this...

18:32.544 --> 18:35.546
all this here is between us now.

18:35.547 --> 18:37.814
Any more players in the pot,

18:37.815 --> 18:40.450
all bets are off the table,
understood?

18:40.451 --> 18:42.555
[Bill]
How can I trust you?

18:43.555 --> 18:45.288
[laughs]

18:45.289 --> 18:48.362
Son, how can I
fucking trust you?

18:51.362 --> 18:53.430
A closed mouth...

18:53.431 --> 18:55.768
admits no flies.

18:56.768 --> 18:58.973
You get the picture?

19:02.973 --> 19:04.877
[laughs]

19:06.877 --> 19:08.484
Get the picture?

19:14.484 --> 19:16.974
[doo-wop playing]

19:36.974 --> 19:39.744
Hey, honey.
Come over here.

19:40.744 --> 19:42.246
Yeah, you. Come on.

19:42.247 --> 19:43.646
Can I help you with something?

19:43.647 --> 19:45.453
I don't bite.
Come on.

19:49.453 --> 19:50.988
Want to do something for me?

19:50.989 --> 19:53.491
- What's that?
- Need some money?

19:54.491 --> 19:55.491
It depends.

19:56.027 --> 19:57.928
Well, you're looking good
tonight.

19:57.929 --> 19:59.729
[both laugh]

19:59.730 --> 20:01.698
Don't tell me.
Not that.

20:01.699 --> 20:05.469
No. Take those in there
and get some money for me.

20:05.470 --> 20:07.008
Why?

20:10.008 --> 20:11.809
Because I like you.

20:12.809 --> 20:14.710
Why can't you do it yourself?

20:14.711 --> 20:16.449
Because I asked you to do it.

20:18.449 --> 20:20.818
It'll be worth your while.

20:21.818 --> 20:23.586
All right.

20:23.587 --> 20:25.457
That's a good girl.

20:26.457 --> 20:27.457
[chuckles]

20:36.433 --> 20:38.367
There you go.

20:38.368 --> 20:39.568
Ah.

20:39.569 --> 20:41.604
[laughs]

20:41.605 --> 20:44.074
I told you it'd be worth
your while.

20:44.075 --> 20:46.375
I hope this doesn't
come back to haunt me.

20:46.376 --> 20:47.943
It won't, babe.

20:47.944 --> 20:49.945
Now that's for you.

20:49.946 --> 20:51.347
[laughs]

20:51.348 --> 20:52.548
You're a prick.

20:52.549 --> 20:53.549
Mm-hmm.

20:57.422 --> 20:59.389
Goodbye.

20:59.390 --> 21:01.924
[Bill] So, how do you know
this fucking weirdo, anyway?

21:01.925 --> 21:03.794
[Roy] You could say
he's a distant uncle.

21:03.795 --> 21:06.095
- An old friend of sorts.
- An uncle?

21:06.096 --> 21:07.596
He's a friend.

21:07.597 --> 21:09.365
He's fucking weird.

21:09.366 --> 21:11.601
- Oh, we go back. Trust me.
- I do trust you.

21:11.602 --> 21:13.603
I just don't trust him.

21:13.604 --> 21:16.440
Just keep thinking
about all the nice things
you can buy afterwards.

21:16.441 --> 21:18.374
That'll ease your mind.

21:18.375 --> 21:19.910
You got plans?

21:19.911 --> 21:21.812
I've been thinking about it.

21:21.813 --> 21:24.349
Yeah. And?

21:25.349 --> 21:26.751
Nah, it's nothing.

21:27.751 --> 21:29.618
Come on, tell me.

21:29.619 --> 21:31.854
You're really not
going to tell me?

21:31.855 --> 21:33.795
All right.

21:37.795 --> 21:39.629
Well, remember a few years back

21:39.630 --> 21:41.597
when we all went
to that old-ass ghost town

21:41.598 --> 21:44.800
with all them stinky-ass burros
walking around?

21:44.801 --> 21:47.069
- Oatman.
- Yeah.

21:47.070 --> 21:50.073
It's the farthest I've ever been
outside this whole desert.

21:50.074 --> 21:52.009
People talk about places
like France and New York

21:53.009 --> 21:54.510
or whatever the fuck.

21:54.511 --> 21:57.447
But, man...

21:57.448 --> 22:02.521
I've never been past
little-ass Oatman, Arizona.

22:04.521 --> 22:06.957
And that's where I'm going
to buy the most beautiful,

22:06.958 --> 22:09.925
bright-red Chevelle.

22:09.926 --> 22:12.432
Something like a '68.

22:15.432 --> 22:18.934
And I'm going to drive that
mother clear across the Mojave,

22:18.935 --> 22:22.986
right until I reach that
one highway next to the ocean.

22:34.986 --> 22:36.594
[turns ignition off]

22:43.594 --> 22:45.566
I told you that son of a bitch
was green.

22:48.566 --> 22:50.600
You know what
I remember you telling me?

22:50.601 --> 22:52.669
Was that there was going to be
a lot more money

22:52.670 --> 22:53.970
than there actually was.

22:53.971 --> 22:55.204
That's what you said.

22:55.205 --> 22:56.672
- Did I say that?
- Yeah.

22:56.673 --> 22:58.975
Well, maybe I got something else

22:58.976 --> 23:02.080
you and your hermano
might be interested in.

23:04.080 --> 23:06.516
He's not my hermano,
motherfucker.

23:06.517 --> 23:07.918
He's my brother.

23:07.919 --> 23:10.720
You're making it
a real bad habit

23:10.721 --> 23:12.999
of wasting my fucking time.

23:21.999 --> 23:25.070
100,000 make it worth
your fucking time?

23:27.070 --> 23:28.939
[chuckles]

23:28.940 --> 23:30.010
There you go.

23:34.010 --> 23:36.613
- [laughs]
- 100,000, motherfucker.

23:36.614 --> 23:38.895
- You better not bullshit me.
- I'm just fucking with you.

23:39.016 --> 23:40.249
- That's all.
- Fucking...

23:40.250 --> 23:42.268
[laughs]
I'm just fucking...

23:57.268 --> 23:58.268
[Bill]
Fuck.

24:02.006 --> 24:03.739
Positive this is the right spot?

24:03.740 --> 24:04.811
Yeah.

24:07.811 --> 24:09.625
- How long has it been?
- Just wait.

24:20.625 --> 24:21.924
[exhales]

24:21.925 --> 24:24.560
- You want a stoke?
- No.

24:24.561 --> 24:26.834
Wait, yeah, give me one.

24:29.834 --> 24:32.669
- I'm going to go for a walk.
- Just don't go too far.

24:32.670 --> 24:34.738
Yeah, you'll see me.

24:34.739 --> 24:36.152
[lighter scratches]

24:48.152 --> 24:52.314
[vehicle approaches]

25:16.314 --> 25:17.589
[car doors close]

25:25.589 --> 25:26.589
Hola.

25:30.361 --> 25:32.095
I see you brought
the gardener, huh?

25:32.096 --> 25:33.296
[laughs]

25:33.297 --> 25:34.998
Where's Dick?

25:34.999 --> 25:37.033
Dick sent us.

25:37.034 --> 25:38.136
So...

25:40.136 --> 25:43.306
go ahead and hand over
the chips.

25:43.307 --> 25:45.174
We've got the paper
in the front seat.

25:45.175 --> 25:46.279
Who's that?

25:48.279 --> 25:49.682
Him?

25:52.682 --> 25:54.883
That's my gardener.

25:54.884 --> 25:58.701
Where's the money?
We do everything right here.

26:43.701 --> 26:46.201
Nice. All right,
what do we got here?

26:46.202 --> 26:48.238
Let's see.

26:48.239 --> 26:50.675
Oh, shit.

26:51.675 --> 26:52.790
Now the fucking money.

27:06.790 --> 27:08.134
What the fuck is this?

27:17.134 --> 27:18.768
Where's the fucking money?

27:18.769 --> 27:21.070
What, you mean this money?

27:21.071 --> 27:22.971
We got people back in town
waiting on us.

27:22.972 --> 27:25.307
So if we don't show up
with our share,

27:25.308 --> 27:27.710
they're going to come looking.

27:27.711 --> 27:28.912
So don't fuck us.

27:28.913 --> 27:31.114
Man, shut the fuck up.

27:31.115 --> 27:33.018
No one gives a fuck about you.

27:34.018 --> 27:36.251
Fucking cunt face.

27:36.252 --> 27:38.354
There ain't no fucking
brigade coming.

27:38.355 --> 27:40.390
[Bill]
Listen to me.
You're making a mistake.

27:40.391 --> 27:42.061
[man]
You made the mistake.

27:45.061 --> 27:46.729
[Bill]
You son of a bitch.

27:46.730 --> 27:49.298
This was a fair fucking deal.

27:49.299 --> 27:51.066
This was a fair deal.

27:51.067 --> 27:53.769
This was a fair fucking deal!

27:53.770 --> 27:55.570
- No, it's over, man.
- Roy, shut the fuck up!

27:56.006 --> 27:57.806
